.md` \| Watch windows, severity/cadence/threshold config (all operator-set), register paths, connector flags; critical_flows shared with quinn's config — one source of truth. \| · ol=\| tool \| `ops-tool-requirements.md` \| CI/CD + telemetry connectors (Harness.io/Datadog candidates), platform control planes, backup access. Explicit non-needs: no destructive DB access even mid-incident, no code writes. \| · ll=`logical/book-requirements.md` candidates: SRE text (**shared dev** extract once, cite twice); shared statistics source (OS-level); continuous-delivery text. Severity conventions, cadences, strategy-risk mappings flagged reasoning-based rule 0.6 until then. · wf:Structure=ship: quinn's GATE PASS locked plan rollback exercised staging deploy playbook strategy verify against dated baselines hold watch window. Any verify failure roll back now, diagnose after. incident: classify (doubt rounds up) smallest safe restore (charter holds data fixes operator-run) comms cadence blameless post-mortem mandatory feeds written why-nots. Recurrence mapped fragility escalates dev design pressure. Standing cadence: dependencies through gates, restores actually run, baselines re-dated, expiries owned alerted. Skipped runs logged skips. platform specifics cite dated playbook section; past staleness horizon, use says so. Ground truth verified runs re-dates playbooks; vendor docs never override reality. Thresholds, cadences, severity definitions operator-adopted config; ops proposes labeled reasoning, enforces what's adopted, surfaces repeated rail friction amendment pressure never silent loosening.